KTTSD is the next Proklam.
The first diference is that KTTSD is implemented as a KDED module.
It is based on Proklam and depricates Proklam.

Author: José Pablo Ezequiel "Pupeno" Fernández <pupeno@kde.org>

KTTSD, KDE Text To Speech Daemon is a plug in based dcop service that allows any KDE (or not-KDE) application to send messages using the dcop interface that later will be spoken.
Among the good things is priority system for warnings, messages and text, texts being long texts that are parsed and offer navegability.
